# Command Registration and Initialization

- The root command is defined in [root.go](mdc:internal/commands/root.go) as `rootCmd`.
- Global flags are set on `rootCmd` in its `init()` function.
- Subcommands are registered by calling `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` in their respective `init()` functions.
- Example: The MCP server command is registered in [startMcpServer.go](mdc:internal/commands/startMcpServer.go) and user commands in [user.go](mdc:internal/commands/user.go).
- The CLI uses the Cobra library for command structure and flag parsing.
- The main entry point ([main.go](mdc:cmd/suprsend/main.go)) calls `commands.Execute()`, which runs the CLI.
